{"questionId": "0c54aae7-15f2-4e7b-a138-cae820ff684e_13", "correctAnswer": "D", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Set the appropriate variable to 0", "content": "For the $y$-intercept, set $x=0$ in $y=\\left(\\tfrac{8}{13}\\right)^{x+1}$: $$y=\\left(\\tfrac{8}{13}\\right)^{0+1}=\\tfrac{8}{13}.$$"}, {"title": "Compute the intercept", "content": "So the $y$-intercept is $\\left(0,\\tfrac{8}{13}\\right)$. That matches choice <strong>D</strong> — <strong>D</strong> is correct."}]}